<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-04-22</DATELINE><TITLE>Respiratory Diseases of Gallinaceous Birds</TITLE><BODY>Respiratory conditions constitute many of the diseases affecting all avian species, including gallinaceous birds. Clinical signs and gross lesions of different respiratory diseases are often similar, and establishing a definitive diagnosis may require ancillary laboratory testing. Determination of a specific diagnosis allows practitioners to select the most effective therapies and to prescribe a management program that prevents recurrence.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>